        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria for MRL 2",
        "description": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) are documented in FDA experimental protocol and match CFD boundary conditions within stated measurement uncertainty. Gradation 2 requires documented correspondence between test and simulation boundary conditions."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA experimental data were collected under controlled conditions with documented flow rates (2–7 L/min), rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM), and glycerol-water blood analog fluid properties. CFD boundary conditions replicate these within measurement uncertainty bands. Gradation 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-oc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
