        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoI acceptance criteria for MRL 2",
        "description": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the clinically accepted metric for pump-induced blood trauma and is directly linked to the regulatory decision criterion (RH < 1). Gradation 2 requires documented justification that QoIs are relevant to the clinical decision."
      },
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the standard metric for evaluating pump-induced hemolysis per ISO 10993-4 and FDA guidance. It directly supports the regulatory decision criterion of relative hemolysis RH < 1 versus predicate device. Gradation 2 is met."
