        "description": "Validation experiments use the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative flow conditions. The validation domain overlaps with the COU operating envelope (flow 2–7 L/min, speed 2000–3500 RPM). Gradation 2 requires documented overlap between validation and COU domains."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device class — under operating conditions spanning the CPB clinical range. The validation domain directly overlaps the COU envelope. Gradation 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-nse",
